Sentencas: A mathematical model is developed and used to investigate the effects of axially distributed current collection on the performance of an anode-supported tubular solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC).
Titulo: The influence of current collection on the performance of tubular anode-supported SOFC cells

Sentencas: The physical model considers coupled fluid and thermal transport within the tube, reactive porous-media flow within the electrodes, electrochemical charge-transfer, thermal transport within the MEA structure, and an electric circuit to represent the current-collection system.
Titulo: The influence of current collection on the performance of tubular anode-supported SOFC cells

Sentencas: Four examples are used to illustrate the model and evaluate current-collection strategies.
Titulo: The influence of current collection on the performance of tubular anode-supported SOFC cells

Sentencas: All the examples consider a particular Ni-YSZ vertical bar YSZ vertical bar LSM-YSZ tube, but with different current collection.
Titulo: The influence of current collection on the performance of tubular anode-supported SOFC cells

Sentencas: The inlet fuel stream is a syngas mixture that results from steam reforming of dodecane.
Titulo: The influence of current collection on the performance of tubular anode-supported SOFC cells

Sentencas: Results show that current collection can strongly affect local performance (i.e., composition, temperature, and current density profiles) along the length of the tube as well as overall performance (i.e., efficiency and utilization).
Titulo: The influence of current collection on the performance of tubular anode-supported SOFC cells
